    name: episcleral layer of eyeball                                         
    def: "The episclera is the outermost layer of the sclera. It is composed  
  of loose, fibrous, elastic tissue and attaches to Tenon's capsule. A        
  vascular plexus is found between the conjunctiva and the sclera consisting  
  of two layers of vessels, the superficial episcleral vessels and the deep   
  episcleral vessels." [Wikipedia:Episcleral_layer]                           
